# Workshop rules / permissions
# Human-readable policy the assistant must follow in this repo.
# Pairs with .codex/hooks.json (enforcement) and AGENTS.md (standards).

[allow]
# Read-only exploration is always allowed.
- read any file in this repo
- read-only catalog search and object lookup
- run validation queries that do not modify data
- create or edit artifacts under outputs/

[require_approval]
# These pause for an explicit human yes.
- catalog write/update/delete (must have a reviewed local diff first)
- running any command that writes to a shared database
- editing a shared stored procedure or view definition
- network access to non-allowlisted endpoints

[block]
# Never allowed.
- exposing PII, credentials, secrets, or production extracts
- creating or altering production indexes
- destructive catalog or database operations
- adding real server, database, linked-server, owner, or proprietary names to any file

[escalation]
# When a rule blocks progress, the assistant should:
- explain what it wanted to do and why it was blocked
- propose the safe alternative (for example, draft a diff to outputs/ for review)
- list the owner question that needs a human answer
